The United States strongly condemns the terrorist attack that took place at the Mogadishu International Airport in Somalia on July 26. The attack resulted in the loss of lives and injuries to United Nations personnel, African Union Mission in Somalia (AMISOM) soldiers, Somali citizens, and others. The United States expresses its condolences to the victims and their families. The United States stands in solidarity with Somalia and its partners in the fight against terrorism, particularly al-Shabaab. The United States remains committed to assisting Somalia in achieving peace, prosperity, and the defeat of terrorist organizations.